com.noctarius.tengi.spi.pooling

Interface ObjectPool<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the pooled object

    public interface ObjectPool<T>
    The ObjectPool interface describes the actual object pool implementation itself. It is used to pre-allocate costly or slow creation processes. The object that is pooled needs to be reusable however it is guaranteed to only be used by one acquirer at a given time. After acquisition, if the object is thread-safe, it might be passed to multiple threads and the thread releasing the object must not be the acquisition thread.

    • Method Detail

      • acquire

        default PooledObject<T> acquire()

        Acquires a pooled object instance. The returns pooled instance might be tested using a configured ObjectValidator and activated using a configured ObjectHandler before being returned.

        The object that is returned is guaranteed to be valid at the time of testing however, if based on network connection or other unreliable system, it still might become invalid at any given point after acquisition.

        Returns:
        the pooled element wrapped into a PooledObject instance

      • acquire

        PooledObject<T> acquire(Consumer<T> activator)

        Acquires a pooled object instance. The returns pooled instance might be tested using a configured ObjectValidator and activated using a configured ObjectHandler.activateObject(Object) before being returned. In addition the given activator will be called and can contain additional runtime based logic.

        The passed in activator is always called before the configured ObjectHandler.activateObject(Object) method.

        The object that is returned is guaranteed to be valid at the time of testing however, if based on network connection or other unreliable system, it still might become invalid at any given point after acquisition.

        Parameters:
        activator - the runtime activator to execute against the object
        Returns:
        the pooled element wrapped into a PooledObject instance

      • release

        default void release(PooledObject<T> object)

        Releases a PooledObject to the pool. The returned object instance might be tested using a configured ObjectValidator but it might also be delayed to the next acquisition phase. However the object is passivated by calling ObjectHandler.passivateObject(Object) before returning it to the available pool again.

        Parameters:
        object - the pooled object to release

      • release

        void release(PooledObject<T> object,
             Consumer<T> passivator)

        Releases a PooledObject to the pool. The returned object instance might be tested using a configured ObjectValidator but it might also be delayed to the next acquisition phase. However the object is passivated by calling ObjectHandler.passivateObject(Object) before returning it to the available pool again. In addition the given passivator will also be called and can contain additional runtime based logic.

        The passed in passivator is always called before the configured ObjectHandler.passivateObject(Object) method.

        Parameters:
        object - the pooled object to release
        passivator - the runtime passivator to execute against the object

      • close

        void close()
        Closes the pool and destroys all pre-allocated object instances. It will also call the ObjectHandler.destroy(Object) method with each of the objects to free any externally acquired or allocated resources assigned to the object instance.

      • create

        static <T> ObjectPool<T> create(ObjectHandler<T> handler,
                                int size)
        Creates a new instance of a non-blocking ObjectPool using the given parameters. The returned instance is fully thread-safe and can also create more elements than the given size however the internal size is never growing and over-capacity elements are only temporary and will be destroyed immediately when released.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the pooled object
        Parameters:
        handler - the ObjectHandler instance to bind
        size - the internal capacity (not maximum capacity)
        Returns:
        the new ObjectPool instance
